<img class="aligncenter wp-image-1378669" src="https://i1.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/MAP-1.jpg?resize=600%2C336&#038;ssl=1" alt="" width="600" height="336" srcset="https://i1.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/MAP-1.jpg?w=300&amp;ssl=1 300w, https://i1.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/MAP-1.jpg?resize=58%2C32&amp;ssl=1 58w, https://i1.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/MAP-1.jpg?resize=260%2C146&amp;ssl=1 260w, https://i1.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/MAP-1.jpg?resize=200%2C112&amp;ssl=1 200w" sizes="(max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px" data-recalc-dims="1" /> Hajiya Binta Umar, the first wife of the Emir of Daura, Alhaji Umar Farouk Umar, is dead. She died in Daura, Katsina, Friday. Hajiya Binta was 70 years. The death of the Emir’s wife was confirmed to journalists by the Sarkin Labaran Daura (Chief Information Officer) of the Emirate Council, Malam Usman Ibrahim, in Daura. He said Hajiya Binta died at about 8:00 a.m. on Friday at the Emir’s palace and has been buried according to Islamic rites. Ibrahim said the funeral prayer was led by the Chief Imam of Daura Central Mosque, Suleiman Salisu. (NAN)  Vanguard   The remains of Hajiya Halima Dauda, a relation of President Muhammadu Buhari were buried on Saturday in Daura. February 10, 2018 In "News" The remains of Sen. Mustapha Bukar has been buried in Daura, Katsina state, on Wednesday. April 4, 2018 In "News" The Presidency on Saturday confirmed the death of two members of President Muhammadu Buhari’s extended family in Daura, Katsina state. February 10, 2018 In "News"